race.comment: SWEET TREATS (4) was edged out in a Class 2 over 1500m at Goulburn two back before a below-par performance at Wagga Riverside last start. Won at her only attempt at 1600m three back at Corowa. Clear top pick on that form. SEBASTIAN'S FLYER (6) has been just fair through the line at his last couple, both over slightly shorter trips. Has a strong record here and has placed three from four at the mile so at the fourth run back he should be peaking. SIR SUBLIME (3) led but knocked up in a similar race to this at Nowra recently. Has raced here at the mile three times for two wins. No surprise to see him back in form today with the blinkers reapplied. LORD FINLAND (2) led but was gone at the furlong last start over 1650m at Moruya. Heywood back on this time - might be a surprise packet. KEN'KER (1) can improve with this step up in distance.
